$ VIM option: cinwords
@ cinwords

`cinwords` contains a list of keywords that start an extra indent when `smartindent` or `cindent` is set

The behavior of `cinwords` is not influenced by → development/vim/options/ignorecase[`ignorecase`]

The default of `cinwords` is `"if,else,while,do,for,switch"`.

sa:
  → development/vim/options 
